article.description: — Quinton Morton-Robertson's 26 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Manchester 111-31 on Monday night.
article.headline: Purdue Fort Wayne beats Manchester 111-31
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- — Quinton Morton-Robertson's 26 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Manchester 111-31 on Monday night. Morton-Robertson was 9 of 11 shooting, including 8 for 9 from distance, for the Mastodons (2-1). Eric Mulder scored 15 points while going 6 of 10 from the floor and added seven rebounds. Deonte Billups finished 4 of 5 from 3-point range and 3 for 3 from the line to finish with 15 points. Mike Elliott finished with five points for the Spartans (0-1). Manchester also got five points from Bryant Smith. Kolby Bullard also had five points. Purdue Fort Wayne visits Northwestern in its next matchup on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
